When using the Create Project with Shared Configuration feature in JIRA 7, I was surprised to find that the original project's Components were not copied over to the new project. This behavior was unexpected. I should be able to move issues from the original project to the new project without configuration changes and without the Component fields being reset to blank.

I understand that the Component is not a part of the configuration that can be shared between projects, but the option should be provided to copy the Component definitions over. Otherwise, I'm faced with the time-consuming and error-prone task of manually re-entering that information.

