*Summary:*
When editing the HTML codes for the Introduction gadget, it was discovered that using the Border class in CSS would change the border settings for all tables in JIRA.

*Screenshot:*
!image-2016-02-24-16-17-44-921.png|thumbnail!  !screenshot-1.png|thumbnail!  
!screenshot-2.png|thumbnail!

*HTML Code:*

{code:java}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>

//Workaround for the border issue
#bdr {
    border: 1px solid black;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    text-align: left;
}

//Code that is causing the error
table, th, td {
    border: 1000px dashed red;   
}

th, td {
    padding: 5px;
}

th {
    background-color: #f0f0f0;
}
</style>
</head>

<body>
<table id=bdr style="width:100%">
  <tr>
    <th id=bdr>Software</th>
    <td id=bdr>Atlassian JIRA</td>		
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <th id=bdr>Administrator</th>
    <td id=bdr>Charlie</td>		
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <th id=bdr>Status</th>
    <td id=bdr><font color=green>Active</font></td>		
  </tr>
</table>
</body>
</html>
</!DOCTYPE>
{code}

*Workaround:*
Use an 'id' tag for individual components.

